Serialized Fields

nodeLabel

XNativeTerm nodeLabel
The externally visible XTerm that this node represents in the constraint graph. May be null, if this promise corresponds to an internal node.

value

XPromise value
This node may have been equated to another node, n. If so, value contains the reference to n. Can be null.

disEquals

java.util.Collection<E> disEquals
Lazily created collection of XPromises to which this one has been disequated.

fields

java.util.Map<K,V> fields
fields captures constraints on fields of this variable, if any. Invariant: if value is not null, then fields must be null, the constraints are translated to the target of the value. We represent composite terms (e.g., binary operators, unary operators, calls) as promises with fields representing the operator and the operands.
